column1: Transect walks should only be carried out in warm and at least bright weather, with no more than moderate winds and not when it is raining.
The minimum criteria are either 13-17ºC with at least 60% sunshine, or if there is no sunshine the temperature must be 17ºC or above.
Windspeed (Beaufort scale) should be no more than 5 unless the transect route is sheltered from the wind.
Do not record if the temperature is below 13ºC.
Check that conditions are suitable before you start the transect, and that if the temperature is less than 17ºC there is likely to be sufficient sun.

column3: Transect counts should ideally be made between 10:45 and 15:45 hours, though between 10:00 and 17:00 hours is usually allowable.
